{"id":2008,"date":"2022-03-15T15:31:34","date_gmt":"2024-03-15T13:18:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/?page_id=2008"},"modified":"2024-06-19T12:22:59","modified_gmt":"2024-06-19T11:22:59","slug":"safeguarding-2","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/parents\/safeguarding-2\/","title":{"rendered":"Safeguarding"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Is Safeguarding?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Safeguarding is defined as \u2013<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Protecting children from maltreatment;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Preventing impairment of children&#8217;s health or development;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ensuring that children are growing up in circumstances consistent with the provision of safe and effective care; and<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Taking action to enable all children to have the best outcomes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"278\" src=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2024\/05\/safeguarding-strapline-1024x278.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2134\" srcset=\"https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2024\/05\/safeguarding-strapline-1024x278.png 1024w, https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2024\/05\/safeguarding-strapline-300x81.png 300w, https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2024\/05\/safeguarding-strapline-768x208.png 768w, https:\/\/leahall.fet.ac\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/6\/2024\/05\/safeguarding-strapline.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Safeguarding pupils is the priority at Lea Hall Academy. If you are ever worried about a child contact The Children&#8217;s Advice and Support Service (CASS) provides a single point of contact for professionals and members of the public who want